<div><h3>ECON 278 - Place and Prospects:  Spatial (In)equality and How it Matters </h3>  <p><hr>This course is designed as a capstone seminar in economics, with priority given to students in economics completing their capstones. The course introduces the student to vigorous debates about the reasons for spatial inequality in urban areas, whether ethnic or racial segregation, environmental injustice, stark gaps in educational achievement between the city and its suburbs, or gentrification of lower - and middle-income neighborhoods.  Consequences of inequality and potential remedies are also discussed. Students are expected to complete a capstone research project on a topic related to spatial inequality over the course of the semester.<br><br><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> <a href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=26&coid=85532" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=26&coid=85532&print', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" rel="remote /ajax/preview_course.php?catoid=26&coid=85532&display_options[location]=tooltip&show" id="tt5959" target="_blank">ECON 010</a><span style="display: none !important">&#160;</span> <a href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=26&coid=85533" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=26&coid=85533&print', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" rel="remote /ajax/preview_course.php?catoid=26&coid=85533&display_options[location]=tooltip&show" id="tt6313" target="_blank">ECON 011</a><span style="display: none !important">&#160;</span> <a href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=26&coid=85540" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=26&coid=85540&print', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" rel="remote /ajax/preview_course.php?catoid=26&coid=85540&display_options[location]=tooltip&show" id="tt2088" target="_blank">ECON 160</a><span style="display: none !important">&#160;</span> <a href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=26&coid=85556" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=26&coid=85556&print', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return 